modules.description: Provides functions to construct and manipulate build configurations, including parsing input specifications, generating dependency graphs, and executing build steps. Operates on custom data structures representing targets, dependencies, and build rules. Used to automate software compilation by defining precise execution sequences based on file changes.

Provides functions to decode S-expressions into OCaml records and lists, using combinators for structured data. Works with S-expressions represented as nested lists and atoms, supporting optional fields and variant types. Enables parsing of complex data like address books into typed OCaml values with precise field matching.

The module offers decoding operations for S-expressions, supporting atoms, lists, records, variants, and recursive structures via combinators that enable sequential parsing, branching, and error handling. It works with S-expressions and a custom `sexp` type, allowing flexible extraction of nested data like tuples, options, and repeated elements. Use cases include parsing configuration files, handling structured data serialization, and processing recursive or variant-rich formats with precise field control.
